{{Infobox person | name= Édouard Ardaillon | birth_date = {{Birth date|1867|5|4}} | birth_place = [[Mazères, Ariège|Mazères]] | nationality = {{FRA}} | death_date = {{death date and age |1926|9|19|1867|5|4}} | death_place = [[Oran]] }}
'''Édouard Muller Ardaillon''' (born 4 May 1867 at [[Mazères, Ariège|Mazères]] in [[Ariège (department)|Ariège]],<ref>[http://mdr-archives.ariege.fr/mdr/index.php/docnumViewer/calculHierarchieDocNum/278273/261748:271983:273637:278273/900/1600 Archives of Ariège, commune of Mazères, birth certificate 44, 1867 (page 85/298)] ( with [http://www.culture.gouv.fr/LH/LH004/PG/FRDAFAN83_OL0047003v017.htm Copy] in the Base Léonore)</ref> died 19 September 1926 at [[Oran]] in [[Algeria]]<ref>[http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k6389115q/f13.image.r=ardaillon%20alger%201926.langFR Obituary in La Vie Algérienne, Tunisienne et Marocaine, 25 September 1926 (Page 9/15)]</ref><ref name=irhis>{{cite book|url=http://hleno.revues.org/116#tocto1n4|title=Les lettrés de la République: Les enseignants de la Faculté des Lettres de Douai puis Lille sous la Troisième République (1870-1940)|first=Jean-François|last=Condette|series=Histoire et littérature de l'Europe du Nord-Ouest|publisher=IRHiS-Institut de Recherches Historiques du Septentrion|date=2006|access-date=12 December 2013|location=Villeneuve d'Ascq|isbn=2-905637-52-8|pages=238}}</ref>) was a French [[historian]], [[archaeologist]] and [[geographer]].
== Career == After graduating from the Boys' Catholic College of Sainte-Marie in [[Saint-André-de-Cubzac]], he undertook a bachelor of arts.<ref>Christophe Meynard, ''Saint André de Cubzac'', édition Sutton, Saint-Cyr sur Loire, 2010</ref> He was a scholar of the [[lycée Louis-le-Grand]] from 1884 to 1887.<ref name=irhis/> In 1887, he enrolled in the [[École Normale Supérieure]] where he achieved the [[Agrégation]] in 1890;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rhe.ish-lyon.cnrs.fr/?q=agregsecondaire_laureats|author=André Chervel|title=Les agrégés de l'enseignement secondaire. Répertoire 1809-1950|work=Resources numériques en histoire de l'éducation|access-date=19 June 2014}}.</ref> he then joined the [[École française d'Athènes]] (graduated 1891).
In 1897, he defended his thesis on the [[mines of Laurion]], the silver mines near [[Athens]], whose rich deposits and intense exploitation played a key role in the development of Athenian power in the [[classical Greece|classical period]]; it still remains a reference work on this subject. He also carried out excavations in the port of [[Delos]] and visited the [[Cyclades]], [[Ionia]], [[Lydia]] and [[Rhodes]]. In June 1894 he married a young Greek girl while he was in Athens, with whom he went on to have two children.<ref name=irhis/>
From November 1896 he was in charge of a geography programme in the [[Charles de Gaulle University – Lille III|faculty of Arts at Lille]],<ref>Michel Sivignon, « Cinquante ans de géographie de la Grèce, d’Élisée Reclus à Jules Sion », ''Bulletin de Correspondance Hellénique'', 123-1, 1999, p.234</ref> where he became Chair of geography in 1899. Under his direction, the geography department of this university became important. His career received the encouragement and support of [[Georges Perrot]], director of l'École normale supérieure; [[Théophile Homolle]], Director of the [[École française d'Athènes]], and [[Charles Bayet]], rector of Lille university.<ref name=irhis/>
In 1905 he became rector of the [[University of Besançon]].<ref>Catherine Valenti, « Les membres de l'École française d'Athènes : étude d'une élite universitaire (1846-1992) », ''Bulletin de Correspondance Hellénique'', 120-1, 1996, p.170</ref> Finally, he was rector of the [[University of Algiers]] from 1908 until his death in 1926.
==Selected publications== * 1893. "Rapport sur le tremblement de terre de Zante" (Report on the [[Zante]] Earthquake), ''[[Annales de géographie]]'' 2(7) 273-280 ([http://www.persee.fr/web/revues/home/prescript/article/geo_0003-4010_1893_num_2_7_7210 Online]) * 1896. "Rapports sur les fouilles du port de Delos" ''[[Bulletin de correspondance hellénique]]'' 20 (1):428-445 ([http://www.persee.fr/web/revues/home/prescript/article/bch_0007-4217_1896_num_20_1_3608 Online]) * 1897. "Répartition des Chrétiens et des Musulmans dans l'île de Crète" (Division of Christians and Muslims on the Island of Crete) ''Annales de Géographie'' 6(27): 255-257. * 1898. ''Les mines du Laurion dans l’Antiquité'' (The Mines of Laurion in Antiquity) Thesis. * 1901. "Les principes de la géographie moderne" (The Principles of Modern Geography) ''Bulletin de la Société de Géographie de Lille'' 35, 269—90. * 1902. ''Carte archéologique de l’île de Délos'' (Archaeological Map of the Island of Delos).
